<asp:Content ID="Content1" ContentPlaceHolderID="main_nav" runat="server">
    <div style="width:577px;">
        <h1>How to change your existing EIS Consulting Microsoft Outlook configuration to connect to the new EIS Consulting Exchange Server</h1>       
        <p>Please make sure you have downloaded and installed our Certificate from <a href="../AMCSCA_CERT_FILE.zip">here</a>. If you need help installing the certificate, please click <a href="Install_Cert.aspx">here</a> for instructions installing.</p>
        <br />
        <p>First make sure Microsoft Outlook is closed.  Then click on the "Start" button and then on "Control Panel".</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image01.PNG" />
        <p>In Control Panel, click on "User Accounts".</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image02.PNG" width="534px" />
        <p>Now click on "Mail".</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image03.PNG" width="534px" />
        <p>The Mail Setup window appears.  Click on the "E-mail Accounts" button.</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image04.PNG" />
        <p>Make sure to click on your account name, and then click the "Change.." button.</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image05.PNG" width="534px" />
        <p>From the "Change Account" dialog, click on the "More Settings ..." button.</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image06.PNG" width="534px" />
        <p>In the "Microsoft Exchange" dialog, click on the "Connection" tab.</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image07.PNG" />
        <p>On the "Connection" tab, click on the "Exchange Proxy Settings..." button.</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image08.PNG" />
        <p>On the "Microsoft Exchange Proxy Settings" dialog, change server name in the two boxes to; "owa.eisconsult.com" and "msstd:owa.eisconsult.com" respectivley, and then click the "OK" button.</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image09.PNG" />
        <p>Next click the "Next", "OK", "Finish" and "Apply" buttons, on each dialog to close out of all of the settings windows saving the settings along the way.</p>
        <img alt="" src="images/Change_Outlook/image10.PNG" width="534px" />
        <p>You can now open Microsoft Outlook with the new settings, and login to view your email.</p>
    </div>
